成績評価方法:
Students will be required to:
1. attend classes regularly, contributing actively to pair work and small group discussions;
2. submit regular in-class summary sheets;
3. successfully complete a listening and speaking test at the end of the semester;
4. successfully complete a written summary test at the end of the semester.

授業の到達目標:
Students should expect to improve their abilities to do the following:
1. read and analyze short articles written in contemporary English;
2. facilitate and participate in discussions of current events with their peers;
3. understand and respond to the way that Japan is reported in contemporary media.

成績評価方法:
Students should expect to:
1. attend the course regularly and contribute actively to discussions;
2. once or twice per semester, choose an article, prepare a short vocabulary list and discussion questions in English, and lead class discussion;
Grades will be based on all of the above. There will be no formal examinations.
If you cannot attend class for any reason, please inform me in advance by e-mail. You may be absent in order to attend job interviews and practice teaching (教育実習), but you must inform me of your plans in advance. Two or more unexplained absences will count against your final grade.
